Oct. 7th
========

ros indigo hosts gazebo 2.2, 
but to use gazebo 4 with ros, refer to:
* http://gazebosim.org/tutorials?tut=ros_wrapper_versions&cat=connect_ros
* http://gazebosim.org/tutorials?tut=ros_installing&cat=connect_ros

then we'll be able to run gazebo through ros:
* roslaunch gazebo_ros gazebo

issue: roslaunch gazebo_ros empty_model.world: process has died
solution: 1) ps ax | grep gzserver and kill pid.

roslaunch gazebo_ros willowgarage_world.launch
roslaunch gazebo_ros mud_world.launch
roslaunch gazebo_ros shapes_world.launch
roslaunch gazebo_ros rubble_world.launch

* http://gazebosim.org/tutorials?tut=ros_roslaunch&cat=connect_ros
note that the package names are: MYROBOT_gazebo and MYROBOT_description.

* to create a catkin package, refer to 
http://wiki.ros.org/ROS/Tutorials/catkin/CreatingPackage

* spawn a model in gazebo
rosrun gazebo_ros spawn_model -file ~/catkin-ws/src/evolutus_description/sdf/chimp-head.sdf -sdf -z 0 -model evolutus

* communication: we can control the models via command prompt. 
http://gazebosim.org/tutorials/?tut=ros_comm

rosservice call /gazebo/apply_joint_effort "joint_name: 'rotator_joint'
effort: 1.0
start_time:
  secs: 0
  nsecs: 0
duration:
  secs: 10
  nsecs: 0"
rosservice call /gazebo/clear_joint_forces '{joint_name: rotator_joint}'
rosservice call /gazebo/pause_physics
rosservice call /gazebo/unpause_physics

netstat -ltpn

